  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Climate Resilience In Indigenous Southern Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Richtersveld World Heritage Site (RWHS) in South Africa is home to the Indigenous Nama people, living in and nearby the park. Climate change threatens the habitats of these communities whose livelihoods and culture depend on natural resources found in their traditional lands. The goal of this program is to scale capacity building for climate adaptation in some of South Africa&apos;s oldest and most vulnerable Indigenous tribes to achieve current and long-term climate resilience.</narrative>
  </description>
